  "name": "Coronary Heart Disease - Revascularization Procedures Query (FIRST Procedure Test)",
  "description": "**FIRST Procedure-resource test in the suite.** Tests ability to find CHD patients via revascularization procedures: CABG (coronary artery bypass grafting), PCI (percutaneous coronary intervention), coronary stent placement, and balloon angioplasty. Procedure resources are distinct from Condition resources \u2014 this exercises a new FHIR resource type. Synthea has historically had reliability issues with Procedure exports (must include `duration` field and non-wellness encounters per past test cases). The CHD module fixes this.",
